accelerator.HelpText: Specify the desired type of accelerator table. Valid options are 'Apple' (.apple_names, .apple_namespaces, .apple_types, .apple_objc), 'Dwarf' (.debug_names), 'Pub' (.debug_pubnames, .debug_pubtypes) and 'Default'
accelerator.Name: accelerator

arch.HelpText: Link DWARF debug information only for specified CPU architecturetypes. This option can be specified multiple times, once for eachdesired architecture. All CPU architectures will be linked bydefault.
arch.Name: arch

assembly.HelpText: Output textual assembly instead of a binary dSYM companion file.
assembly.Name: S

dump_debug_map.HelpText: Parse and dump the debug map to standard output. Not DWARF link will take place.
dump_debug_map.Name: dump-debug-map

flat.HelpText: Produce a flat dSYM file (not a bundle).
flat.Name: flat

gen_reproducer.HelpText: Generate a reproducer consisting of the input object files.
gen_reproducer.Name: gen-reproducer

keep_func_for_static.HelpText: Make a static variable keep the enclosing function even if it would have been omitted otherwise.
keep_func_for_static.Name: keep-function-for-static

no_odr.HelpText: Do not use ODR (One Definition Rule) for type uniquing.
no_odr.Name: no-odr

no_output.HelpText: Do the link in memory, but do not emit the result file.
no_output.Name: no-output

no_swiftmodule_timestamp.HelpText: Don't check timestamp for swiftmodule files.
no_swiftmodule_timestamp.Name: no-swiftmodule-timestamp

object_prefix_map.HelpText: Remap object file paths (but no source paths) before processing.Use this for Clang objects where the module cache location wasremapped using -fdebug-prefix-map; to help dsymutilfind the Clang module cache.
object_prefix_map.Name: object-prefix-map

oso_prepend_path.HelpText: Specify a directory to prepend to the paths of object files.
oso_prepend_path.Name: oso-prepend-path

output.HelpText: Specify the output file. Defaults to <input file>.dwarf
output.Name: o

papertrail.HelpText: Embed warnings in the linked DWARF debug info.
papertrail.Name: papertrail

remarks_output_format.HelpText: Specify the format to be used when serializing the linked remarks.
remarks_output_format.Name: remarks-output-format

remarks_prepend_path.HelpText: Specify a directory to prepend to the paths of the external remark files.
remarks_prepend_path.Name: remarks-prepend-path

statistics.HelpText: Print statistics about the contribution of each object file to the linked debug info. This prints a table after linking with the object file name, the size of the debug info in the object file (in bytes) and the size contributed (in bytes) to the linked dSYM. The table is sorted by the output size listing the object files with the largest contribution first.
statistics.Name: statistics

symbolmap.HelpText: Updates the existing dSYMs inplace using symbol map specified.
symbolmap.Name: symbol-map

symtab.HelpText: Dumps the symbol table found in executable or object file(s) and exits.
symtab.Name: symtab

threads.HelpText: Specifies the maximum number of simultaneous threads to use when linking multiple architectures.
threads.Name: num-threads

toolchain.HelpText: Embed toolchain information in dSYM bundle.
toolchain.Name: toolchain

update.HelpText: Updates existing dSYM files to contain the latest accelerator tables and other DWARF optimizations.
update.Name: update

use_reproducer.HelpText: Use the object files from the given reproducer path.
use_reproducer.Name: use-reproducer

verify.HelpText: Run the DWARF verifier on the linked DWARF debug info.
verify.Name: verify

yaml_input.HelpText: Treat the input file is a YAML debug map rather than a binary.
yaml_input.Name: y
